png

Class PngChunkTIME2

  • java.lang.Object
    • png.PngChunk
      • png.PngChunkTIME2

  • public class PngChunkTIME2
extends PngChunk
    Encapsulates the tIME ancillary chunk, which records the last modification time of the image content. *

    According to ISO/IEC 15948:2004, the tIME chunk contains 7 bytes representing the UTC time. This class validates that each field (Year, Month, Day, Hour, Minute, Second) falls within the legal ranges specified by the PNG standard.

      • getModificationDate

        public java.util.Date getModificationDate()
        Converts the binary fields into a Java Date object.

        Note: PNG tIME is always UTC. Java Calendar months are 0-based (January is 0), so this method automatically offsets the PNG month (1-12).

        Returns:
        a Date object representing the modification time in UTC
